REQUEST FOR PROPOSALS &ndash; Data and Application Modernization (DAM) Pre-Qualification Refresh List&nbsp;

ABOUT FCC
FCC is Canada&rsquo;s leading agriculture and food lender, dedicated to the industry that feeds the world. FCC employees are committed to the long-standing success of those who produce and process Canadian food by providing flexible financing, AgExpert business management software, information and knowledge. FCC provides a complement of expertise and services designed to support the complex and evolving needs of food businesses. As a financial Crown corporation, FCC is a stable partner that reinvests profits back into the industry and communities it serves. For more information, visit fcc.ca.

RFP CONTACT

Ronke Niagwan
Procurement Manager
Farm Credit Canada
procurement@fcc.ca

RFP SCOPE
FCC&rsquo;s Information Technology (IT) team is accountable for enabling and delivering IT Services to FCC&rsquo;s community and enterprise leaders to enable execution excellence.  To effectively meet its business objectives, FCC often augments its internal staff.  As part of this RFP, FCC will select a list of Vendors who will reside on our Pre-Qualified (PQ) List for Data and Application Modernization.&nbsp;&nbsp;
FCC has a suite of products that are either used internally by FCC employees and contractors or externally by customers. FCC intends to modernize these Products using a phased approach. Currently, the majority of the Products and Software are Thin Client-based and FCC intends to make them Web-based. FCC is also moving from a traditional data warehouse model to AWS pipeline data infrastructure.&nbsp;
The objective of the RFP is to establish a list of Vendors that FCC can leverage who are experienced and have a successful history of Product Modernization and Data Engineering. This list will also allow FCC to scale resource capacity with flexibility and agility. FCC expects increased business value, through supporting mutually beneficial relationships with vendors on the PQ List over time. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
FCC sees the successful Proponent(s), as part of the Pre-Qualified List (or PQ List) being able to provide Data and Application Modernization Services in the future. Such services will include but are not limited to the following: &nbsp;

	Data Modernization&nbsp;
	Application Modernization&nbsp;
	Roadmapping &nbsp;
	Architecture Assessments &nbsp;
	Feasibility Studies &nbsp;



	Migration&nbsp;
